<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:09PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Broadwater and central Jefferson Counties through 445 PM MDT...
At 408 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Walkerville, or 8 miles northeast of Butte, moving northeast at 50
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph, pea size hail, and brief heavy
rain showers.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Boulder, Basin, Elkhorn State Park and Elk Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
